examples.en: Each number corresponds to a location on the map.
Her photograph corresponds with the description that he gave us.
Determinate vapour pressure corresponds to determinate temperature.
In some countries, the role of president corresponds to that of prime minister.
The scientist corresponds with colleagues in order to learn about matters relevant to her own research.
One "bit" is the smallest amount of data which can exist, and corresponds to the answer to a yes-or-no question.
